</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[192,1440,796,1141]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,338,796,820]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Definition.</emphasis>
A genus related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Godman and Salvin, 1896" authorityName="Godman and Salvin" authorityYear="1896" box="[569,997,796,820]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Zopyrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[569,678,797,820]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Zopyrion</emphasis>
Godman and Salvin, 1896
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[1011,1065,797,821]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Godman and Salvin, [1896]" authorityName="Godman and Salvin" authorityYear="1896" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Zopyrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sandace">
<emphasis box="[1163,1376,796,820]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Zopyrion sandace</emphasis>
Godman and Salvin, [1896]
</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="Godman and Salvin, 1896" authorityName="Godman and Salvin" authorityYear="1896" box="[502,972,828,852]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Timochreon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[502,647,828,852]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Timochreon</emphasis>
Godman and Salvin, 1896
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[987,1041,829,853]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName box="[1143,1318,828,852]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Helias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="satyrus">
<emphasis box="[1143,1318,828,852]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Helias satyrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
C. and R. Felder, [1867]), and 
<taxonomicName authority="Mabille, 1876" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1876" box="[440,760,860,885]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Anisochoria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[440,586,860,884]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Anisochoria</emphasis>
Mabille, 1876
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[776,830,861,885]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Mabille, 1876" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1876" box="[931,1378,860,885]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Anisochoria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polysticta">
<emphasis box="[931,1201,860,884]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Anisochoria polysticta</emphasis>
Mabille, 1876
</taxonomicName>
, now considered a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Butler, 1870))" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Butler" baseAuthorityYear="1870" box="[521,1008,892,917]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Anisochoria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pedaliodina">
<emphasis box="[521,820,892,916]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Anisochoria pedaliodina</emphasis>
(Butler, 1870))
</taxonomicName>
with its junior subjective synonym 
<taxonomicName authority="Bryk, 1953" authorityName="Bryk" authorityYear="1953" box="[192,455,925,949]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Dicrosema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[192,319,925,948]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Dicrosema</emphasis>
Bryk, 1953
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[469,522,925,949]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Bryk, 1953" authorityName="Bryk" authorityYear="1953" box="[618,1091,924,949]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Dicrosema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrifenestrata">
<emphasis box="[618,953,924,948]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Dicrosema quadrifenestrata</emphasis>
Bryk, 1953
</taxonomicName>
), but without obvious affinity to either one of these genera (
<figureCitation box="[564,638,957,981]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="18.[192,275,938,960]" captionTargetBox="[192,1437,214,903]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[192,1440,213,904]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 7. Genomic trees of Pyrgini. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677249" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677249/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Keys to E. 
<quantity box="[785,874,957,981]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.51892" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" unit="in" value="59.8">59.8 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[883,1048,957,981]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" pagination="26 - 53" refId="ref27534" refString="Evans, W. H. 1953. A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part III. Pyrginae. Section 2. British Museum (Natural History); London. v + 246 p., pl. 26 - 53" type="book chapter" year="1953">Evans (1953)</bibRefCitation>
. Morphologically, distinguished from its relatives by almost symmetric valvae with smaller unmodified harpe, ampulla without a process (just with a small knob), and uncus with a pair of short and thin processes at its distal end, between the arms that are widely set apart. Hindwing above with a wide whitish area. In DNA, a combination of the following base pairs is diagnostic: aly8048.1.4:A65G, aly3881.2.1:A178G, aly1097.18.4:G805C, aly 
<date box="[228,335,1117,1141]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" value="1443-03-04">1443.3.4</date>
:T238T (not G), aly 
<date box="[563,670,1117,1141]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" value="1443-03-04">1443.3.4</date>
:C239C (not A), aly890.35.8:T164T (not A).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="18" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="19.[192,1440,1165,1222]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,347,1165,1189]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name, a masculine noun in the nominative singular, is a fusion of 
<emphasis box="[1197,1224,1165,1189]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">br</emphasis>
[unneis], 
<emphasis box="[1337,1352,1166,1189]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">a</emphasis>
[lbum], and 
<emphasis box="[246,271,1197,1221]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">lu</emphasis>
[teu] 
<emphasis box="[328,340,1198,1221]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">s</emphasis>
: the three colors of the 
<typeStatus box="[628,681,1198,1222]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">type</typeStatus>
species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[192,707,1245,1270]" box="[192,707,1245,1270]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,432,1245,1269]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Species included.</emphasis>
Only the 
<typeStatus box="[553,606,1246,1270]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">type</typeStatus>
species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[192,780,1293,1317]" box="[192,780,1293,1317]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,380,1293,1317]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Parent taxon.</emphasis>
Tribe 
<taxonomicName authority="Burmeister, 1878" authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1878" box="[460,776,1293,1317]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Pyrgini">Pyrgini Burmeister, 1878</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[192,1255,1341,1366]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[192,1255,1341,1366]" box="[192,1255,1341,1366]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,345,1341,1365]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Comments.</emphasis>
Yet another genus that would be difficult to detect without DNA analysis.
</paragraph>
